name: Alternative
description: Evaluation computes alternative weights using expert judgments of how wll an alternative addresses leaf criteria

name: properties
description: Alternative properties. E.g. cost, safety rating, ... Properties can be used to assist in expert judgements and also to visualize "alternative space". E.g. cost might be a property which does not taken into account in judgments, rather it is used to build cost/benefit chart.

name: Comparable
description: Something that can be compared - criteria for importance, alternatives for meeting criteria, experts for weight in the evaluation or a particular criterion in the evaluation

name: receivedJudgments
description: Judgments in which this comparable is a target

name: Criterion
description: A criterion for choosing one of alternatives. Criteria may form a hierarchy.

name: alternativeFormula
description: SpEL (Spring Expression Language) expression used to compute alternative weight, e.g. from properties.

name: inheritExpertWeights
description: If true, expert weights computed from judgments are multiplied by expert weights inherited from the container. If false, expert weights in the container are not taken into account.

name: alternativeJudgments
description: Judgments to compute weights of alternatives

name: subCriteria
description: Child criteria of this criterion

name: expertJudgments
description: Judgments to assign weight to experts to be used in criteria and alternative judgments. If empty, expert weights are inherited from the container or set to all equal depending on inheritExpertWeights value.

name: subCriteriaJudgments
description: Judgments to compute weights of sub-criteria

name: ExpertGroup
description: Group is a composite expert. E.g. "Security", "Business". Groups can be used to transitively assign expert weights to criteria. E.g. "Security" group may have little or no weight in "Business Functionality" criteria.

name: members
description: Group members, may include other groups so experts may form a hierarchy.

name: expertJudgments
description: Judgments to assign weight to experts in this group. If empty, all experts get the same weight.

name: Judgment
description: Expert judgment regarding target(s) expressed as a double value. If there is one target, then value is a weight of the target. If there are two targets, then value reflects preference of the first value over the second. E.g. 1 would mean that targets are equal, 2 that the first is twice "better" than the second, and 0.5 would mean that the second is twice "better" than the first.

name: value
description: Judgment value. If there is one target, then value is a weight of the target. If there are two targets, then value reflects preference of the first value over the second. E.g. 1 would mean that targets are equal, 2 that the first is twice "better" than the second, and 0.5 would mean that the second is twice "better" than the first.

name: targets
description: Judgment targets - one for weights and two for pair-wise comparisons

name: expert
description: Expert who cast the judgment
